                <head>339. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On December 13, elections for the offices of President and Vice President were
                    held by the Greek and Turkish communities. Archbishop
                        <persName>Makarios</persName> was elected President of the new republic and
                    Dr. Fazil Kuchuk, running unopposed, was elected Vice President. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BTG1">Belcher</persName> commented on the issues involved in the
                    elections in telegram 224 from Nicosia, November 27. (Department of State,
                    Central Files, 747C.00/11–2759) He analyzed the results of the elections in
                    telegram 256 from Nicosia, December 16. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.,
                    747C.00/12–1659)</p>
            </div>
